title.gco:CharacterString: Digital Map of District Boundaries of India, 1971

abstract.gco:CharacterString: This layer is a polygon theme representing district boundaries of India for 1971. Includes district socio-demographic Census attribute data such as total population, population by sex, and rural/urban populations. This layer is part of the India Historical Boundaries dataset showing decadal change in district boundaries of India since 1971. This data layer is sourced from secondary government sources, chiefly Survey of India, Census of India, Election Commission, etc. Includes data for 357 districts, 23 states and 7 union territories.
